Ifo Sees Record German Tax Revenue, Euro Am Sonntag Reports

-- B y   R a g n h i l d   K j e t l a n d
-- 
2011-07-23T09:56:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-23/ifo-sees-record-german-tax-revenue-euro-am-sonntag-reports.html
Germany ’s  Ifo Institute  expects the
country’s tax revenue to reach a record in 2011,  Euro am Sonntag 
reported.  The institute expects tax revenue of 565 billion euros
($811 billion) and 570 billion euros, Euro am Sonntag said,
citing Ifo tax expert Christian Breuer.  In 2008, the strongest year so far in tax revenue, the
state collected 561 billion euros, the weekly newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story: Ragnhild Kjetland in
Frankfurt at   rkjetland@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Kenneth Wong in Berlin at 
